DECODING NFT’s & AIO FANS CLUB with @manit_unofficial and @radhikabhuptani 💰

NFT’s are Non-Fungible Tokens that are set to revolutionise the digital financial markets for the art and entertainment industry 🎬

Here, @manit_unofficial , founder of @aio_fans breaksdown the concept for us along with explaining the perks and idea behind the 1st FAN ENGAGEMENT PLATFORM bridging a gap between the stars and the fans ⭐️

Through the platform, www.market.aiofans.com, we can buy the NFTs of Posters of the regional Gujarati movie Satham Aatham. In the coming weeks, they are going to be launching more NFTs for the audience to buy. Their goal is to launch 1000 NFT’s in the coming 1 year, as per the market analysis 🪙 

With the purchase of the NFT’s comes the exclusive advantages like attending the movie premiere with the stars, getting signed star merchandise, discounts and coupons on some valuable lifestyle brands in the country and a lot more 🎉

Did you know Gujarati’s are the highest investors in the crypto market. So, when are you investing in these NFT’s❓

The only time A'town slows down is winter evenings and that too, to enjoy the starry nights with good food and company. And Vertù - The Lounge ( @vertu.thelounge ) is just the place! One of our favourite rooftop cafe restaurants, it's won our hearts with the ambience, eclectic menu and service. 
 
Spread over a vast area, the uber Instagram-able eatery has a warm and vibrant vibe - perfect for winter evenings. And the food is droolacious! 
 
So shake out that trendy winter jacket and make your way to this beautiful space for a winter evening date. 
 
📍: 5th floor, Silver Radiance One, Zydus hospital road, Thaltej
🕰: 12pm - 10pm 
📞: +91 81818 10299

#TOSEvent 

It was an evening that gave us the kind of high that a sugar binge does! That's literally the best way to describe the TOS exclusive event to mark the launch of macaron chef Pooja Dhingra's ( @poojadhingra ) latest book Coming Home. 

Pastry chef extraordinaire, entrepreneur, podcast host and author of five books, @poojadhingra brought her Coming Home tour to A'town and TOS was elated to be the event partner (again). The book launch saw attendees cheer Pooja through the official book unveiling and watch in rapt attention as she gave a quick demo of her Fennel Cookies (they're yum btw). To ensure her fans got a chance to interact with Pooja, we followed up with an interactive session and a book signing followed by a high tea. Popups and a specially designed photo booth added to the festive vibes of the evening. 

A huge shoutout to all our partners who made the evening possible and all of you who turned up at the event - you were and are the best audience ever. 

P.S If you haven't gotten your copy of the book yet, we'd recommend you grab it right away to add your personal touch to the upcoming festivities.

We often forget to thank our fathers, the silent anchors, the steady hands, the first examples of strength and purpose.
They lead, they guide, and sometimes, without even knowing it, we follow✨

This Father’s Day, through In His Footsteps, we’re celebrating stories where his legacy isn’t just remembered, it’s lived.

And we begin with one of the rarest stories in India - Dr. #SudhirShah and his daughters Dr. Heli Shah and Dr. Chetsi Shah, a father-daughter trio of neurologists whose shared passion for the mind reflects an extraordinary bond of family, purpose, and practice💯

Watch their story, feel the legacy and take a moment to thank the one who led your way ✨

Do you also remember the Boomer pack? Or the iconic Frooti tetrapack with those chunky fonts and wild colors? 🫧🧃

In today’s digital world, we’re all just scrolling… until something grabs our attention👀✨
That’s why maximalism is back - louder, brighter, bolder than ever.

In a sea of muted tones and curated calm, people are craving chaos, the good kind.
The kind that feels like 90s candy aisles, early 2000s ad breaks, and dopamine on print📺💥

Design isn’t just about looking good anymore.
It’s about making you feel something.
And in 2025, more is more. 💡🌈
